headline: CME Crypto Derivatives Average Volume Hit Record $11.3B in Q1
summary: A surge in micro futures trading pushed CME’s crypto derivatives volume to the new quarterly record.

headline: CME Group Sets New, All-Time Quarterly ADV Record of 29.8 Million Contracts, Driven by Growth Across All Asset Classes
summary: CME Group, the world's leading derivatives marketplace, today reported its Q1 and March 2025 market statistics, with average daily volume (ADV) reaching a new, all-time quarterly record of 29.8 million contracts and the second-highest March ADV on record with 30.8 million contracts.
